name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
notes:

Be prepared to show confirmation of your appointment or you may experience a slightly longer wait. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. Ingresar por la puerta 12 en la avenida Pacífico. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. ***THOSE WHO GET THEIR 1ST MODERNA SHOT WILL NEED TO FIND OTHER ARRANGEMENTS TO RECEIVE THEIR SECOND DOSE BY FINDING A CLINIC AT THE WEBSITE PROVIDED.

If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
notes:
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. *** All patients 12 years old and older can register regardless of phase. (If 12-17 years old must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. Enter the building at the time of your appointment only. 
***Residents from ANY state are now eligible to receive the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Arlington Airport Covid-19 Vaccine Site
notes:
Everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination.

Please also note that, even if you are otherwise eligible, you must be 18 or older for the Moderna or Johnson & Johnson vaccine, and 12 or older for the Pfizer vaccine (parent/guardian must be present to sign the consent form).

Appointments are highly recommended but not required.  Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves.

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Benton Franklin - Kennewick COVID Vaccine Clinic
notes: ******Pfizer Clinic***** All patients 16 years old and older can register. If you are 16-17 years old you must be with a parent or guardian or verbal parental/guardian consent. **FOR 2ND DOSE PLEASE BRING YOUR COVID-19 VACCINATION RECORD CARD** For Both 1st and 2nd dose - Please bring your appointment confirmation. Please do not come if you are feeling ill. Given the limited supply of COVID-19 vaccine available at this time and Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location you must either live or work in Washington state. If you do not live or work in Washington, please do not make an appointment or travel to this site. You may be asked to provide something that shows you live or work in Washington, such as a utility bill; a voucher from your employer; or your work, school, or state ID. The site will not make a copy or record this information in any way. This is only to show that you currently live or work in Washington. ---- **Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided. Follow posted signage about traffic and parking at the site. **Enter the fairgrounds from 10th Street.** If you have lost your vaccination record card, please go to https://wa.myir.net
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Harrison Square Presbyterian Church
notes:
****This is a JOHNSON & JOHNSON single dose vaccine clinic. **** and is by appointment or walk in. ++Pfizer vaccine will also be available. ++ 
Please note: Johnson & Johnson vaccine can only be administered to individuals 18 years of age or older according CDC requirements. Pfizer can be administered to youth ages 16 to 17 if accompanied by an adult who can sign a parental consent form.

This clinic is located at and hosted by Harrison Square Presbyterian Church in partnership with Lewis County DPHSS, WA DOH and WA National Guard. This is a walk in location. Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind.  **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation.

Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided.

If this is your 2nd dose Pfizer vaccination please bring your vaccination card from your 1st dose. If you do not have your card you may register with and confirm proof of vaccination at https://wa.myir.net/                      
 Please do not come if you are feeling ill. Please arrive as close as possible to your scheduled time to prevent crowding that will impede appropriate social distancing. - It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. Given Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location must either live or work in Washington state. If you do not live or work in Washington, please do not make an appointment or travel to this site.  **Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine - COVID Vaccine Clinic
notes:
Please read the following important information below:
***We currently have the ability to provide the 1st and 2nd doses of Moderna.***
Please sign up for an appointment time.  

When you arrive to the clinic, please continue to wear your face covering, practice physical distancing and wash your hands frequently to help reduce transmission.

Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. 
Expect to stay for 15 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. 

Due to the limited supplies of vaccines provided to us each week, we are unable to take walk-ins, so please make an appointment. 

***Directions to the Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine:***
Our clinic is located in the Hidden Valley Office Complex.
1) When you arrive at the complex, take either driveway all the way to the back of the building.
2) We are located on the prominent corner at the very back of the building and we have our own private entrance.  Look for the parking lot with the number "2" in a big steel frame.  Do NOT go into the main building for we have a private entrance accessible directly from the parking lot. 
Look for our sign with our logo in the window and a door with the number "C-102" on it, visible from the parking lot.

*If you would like to find out more information about our clinic, please visit our website at www.hawkerhealth.com
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
